OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F383A1749840343
OL,3,CMan died due to ambulance crew's
OL,4,C'gross failure in basic care'
OL,6,F"This was a gross failure on their
OL,7,Fpart when the need of a patient in
OL,8,Ftheir care should have been obvious.
OL,10,F"Had Frazer received the care that
OL,11,Fshould have been provided to him ...
OL,12,Fhe would not have suffered a cardiac
OL,13,Farrest and he would not have died. His
OL,14,Fdeath was a result of neglect by the
OL,15,Fambulance crew."
OL,17,FSpeaking earlier at the inquest, Mr
OL,18,FIrvine's mother Linda said: "In those
OL,19,Flast moments ... I only hope he knew
OL,20,Fhow much he was loved.
