OL,3,CMan died due to ambulance crew's
OL,4,C'gross failure in basic care'
OL,6,FIn response to the Coroner's findings,
OL,7,Fthe States of Jersey Ambulance Service
OL,8,Fsays: "We wish to express our sincere
OL,9,Fcondolences to Mr Irvine's family and
OL,10,Floved ones. They have shown dignity
OL,11,Fand patience throughout this difficult
OL,12,Fprocess, and we recognise the deep and
OL,13,Flasting impact this incident has had.
OL,15,F"The care provided to Mr Irvine on the
OL,16,Fnight of 18 March 2022 fell short of
OL,17,Fthe professional standards that the
OL,18,FStates of Jersey Ambulance Service
OL,19,Fexpects and that our community rightly
OL,20,Fdeserves.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G8/9
